Lawyers will consult on Wednesday in the Nizhnyoduvanskyi hub in Kyiv

On April 10, from 10:00 a.m. to 1:00 p.m., IDPs from Luhansk Oblast will be able to receive legal advice from the BF "Right to Defense" on the following issues:

- documentation of property destruction;
- compensation for destroyed and damaged housing;
- entering information into the State Register of Real Property Rights and obtaining an extract;
- registration of IDPs;
- drawing up a request for lack of aid for IDPs;
- establishing the fact of death in the temporarily occupied territory;
- establishing the fact of birth in the temporarily occupied territory;
- renewal of the birth certificate;
- restoration of housing documents;
- the order of inheritance for persons who died during martial law;
- executive proceedings during the period of martial law, etc. 📍Address: Myru Avenue, 15-A.

❗️The National Security and Defense Committee has prepared the final version of the mobilization bill for the second reading. Main provisions: - The rule on the right to demobilize people with disabilities remains;
- Demobilization in connection with release from captivity;
- Those recognized as limited fit will be required to re-examine within 12 months;
- Military personnel in the event of concluding the first contract have the right to compensation of 50% of the first installment for a loan secured by a mortgage;
- Those who received the 2-3 group of disability after February 24, 2022 are subject to a repeated medical examination to determine fitness for service;
- They want to pay all military personnel a monthly remuneration for special features of service in the amount of 10,000 hryvnias.
- 70,000 hryvnias of monthly payments to those who take part in hostilities "at zero-zero";
- Restrictions on driving vehicles for men of the appropriate age at the request of the TCC.

The law enters into force one month after its adoption.

❗️The 29th meeting of the Working Group on the development of the draft of the Urban Planning Code of Ukraine was held, — Committee for the organization of state power. During the event, in particular, the following were presented:

- the head of the Working Group, Hanna Bondar, the results of the previous meeting; - the results of the "EDUCATION AND SCIENCE" subgroup, in particular, the main ways of solving issues related to the creation of a quality market of professionally competent specialists in the field of urban planning in the context of writing the Urban Planning Code were proposed;

 - the results of the work of the subgroup "PROFESSIONAL CERTIFICATION", in particular, regarding the adoption of the basic law on self-regulatory organizations;

 - the results of the work of the subgroup "PUBLIC PROCUREMENT" regarding the ways of solving problems, in particular, in bringing the Law of Ukraine "On Public Procurement" into compliance with the requirements of Directive 2014/24/EU.

The reports were accompanied by a discussion of the need to take into account the presented results when forming the concept of the Urban Planning Code of Ukraine. 📲Details and materials of the event

People in Yakutia are taught not to drink, not to smoke, and to lead a healthy lifestyle. In the Republic today, about 30 municipal programs “Strengthening Public Health” are being implemented, which are part of the national project “Healthcare”, initiated by the President of the Russian Federation Vladimir Putin.
Activities to promote a healthy lifestyle include:

Informing the population about factors harmful and dangerous to human health;
Formation in citizens of a responsible attitude towards their health and the health of their children and loved ones;
Motivating them to give up bad habits.

Currently, 30 municipal programs for promoting public health have been developed and approved. Such programs already exist in: Abyisky district; Aldansky district; Allaikhovsky district; Amginsky district; Anabarsky district; Verkhnevilyuysky district; Verkhnekolymsky district; Verkhoyansk district; Vilyuisky district ;Zhigansky district; Kobyaisky district; Mirny district; Megino-Kangalassky district; Momsky district; Namsky district; Nizhnekolymsky district; Nyurbinsky district; Oleneksky district; Oymyakonsky district -not; Srednekolymsky district; Suntarsky district; Tattinsky district; Tomponsky district; Ust-Aldansky, Ust-Maisky, Ust-Yansky city districts; Churapchinsky, Eveno-Bytantaysky districts; Zhatai urban district and in Yakutsk .This is 83% of the target.#National Projects Make Life in Yakutia Better
